-- Anglo American, BHP, Racec, Sasol: South African Equity Preview
-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 2010-12-22T06:07:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/anglo-american-bhp-pinnacle-south-african-stocks-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose to the
highest level since May 2008, climbing 331.29, or 1 percent, to
32,063.81 at the close in Johannesburg.  Anglo American Plc  (AGL SJ) and  BHP Billiton Plc  (BIL SJ):
Copper rose to the highest level since at least December 1988 in
London. Anglo jumped 8.63 rand, or 2.6 percent, to 342.48 rand,
while BHP climbed 1.4 percent to 270.75 rand.  Chemical Specialities Ltd.  (CSP SJ): The paint manufacturer
said it posted a loss of 46.8 million rand ($7 million) in the
six months through September, widening from a loss of 12.1
million rand a year earlier. Shares in the company fell 3 cents,
or 6.5 percent, to 43 cents, the lowest since Dec. 8.  Pinnacle Point Group Ltd.  (PNG SJ): The resort and leisure
development company said its loss after-tax for the six months
through August narrowed to 74.2 million rand from 306 million
rand a year earlier. The company also said unspecified price-
sensitive talks were continuing. Shares in Pinnacle declined 1
cent, or 50 percent, to 1 cent.  Racec Group Ltd.  (RAC SJ): The rail and civil engineering
company posted a profit of 12.9 million rand for the 12 months
through Sept. 30, compared with a loss of 13.2 million rand a
year earlier. The shares closed unchanged at 58 cents.  Sasol Ltd.  (SOL SJ): Crude rose for a fourth day as signs
of a U.S. economic recovery stoked speculation that fuel demand
will increase in the world’s largest oil consumer. Sasol, the
world’s largest maker of motor fuels from coal, climbed 2.29
rand, or 0.7 percent, to 336 rand.  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) climbed 3.6 percent to
$25.23. AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) dropped 0.8 percent to
$47.88. BHP Billiton Ltd. (BBL US) rose 2.1 percent to $79.63.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) gained 0.2 percent to $4.88. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) fell 1.6 percent to $17.56. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) declined 2.6 percent to $12.13. Impala Platinum
Holdings Co. (IMPUY US) advanced 2.2 percent to $34.50. Sappi
Ltd. (SPP US) added 2.6 percent to $5.07. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US)
rose 0.7 percent to $49.19. Telkom South Africa Ltd. (TLKGY US)
climbed 2.1 percent to $21.90.  To contact the reporter on this story:
